<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4352: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-30T17:00:00-05:00">September 30, 1941—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 1—9:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>185. Your instruction number 198, September 20. Amortization Moratorium
                            Agreement signed today.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>[For the text of Supplementary Financial Agreement between the United
                                States and Haiti, signed at Port-au-Prince, September 30, 1941, see
                                Executive Agreement Series No. 224, or 55 Stat. (pt. 2) 1385.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>